==Hindi==
===Demonstrative pronoun===
'''इस''' (is)

# [[this]] - [[oblique]] case only, see below for direct. (Plural: [[इन]])
#:Example: "इस मकान [[में]] [[छह]] कमरे है" - In this house there are six rooms. Literally - "This house in six rooms are."
# [[him]] - oblique case only, near reference. (If [[respect]] is conveyed, इन is used)
#:Example: "इसको [[पैसे]] [[देना|दे]] [[दो]]" - Give money to him. Literally "Him to money give."
# [[her]] - oblique case only, near reference. (If [[respect]] is conveyed, इन is used)
#:Example "इसको पैसे दे दो" - Give money to her. (The same)
# [[it]] - oblique case only.
#:Example "इस [[लेना|लो]]" - Take it.

====Inflection====
[[Direct]]: [[यह]]

===See also===
*[[उस]](us) - [[That]], [[him]] and [[her]] (far reference).

